Do NOT come here. Horrible service and employees.  Came in yesterday at 330am and was told they were closed for another half hour.... although it's a 24 hr place? Then decided to give it a 2nd chance today. I walked in at 445am and said good morning just to be greated by "what do you want?" I let it go and ordered a dark roast coffee and an everything bagel with cream cheese. The coffee tasted old and was told it it would be another 10 min to brew a fresh batch. The cream cheese was placed on the side and when I asked for my receipt, she rolled her eyes and sighed loudly like I was bothering her.

Waited 15 min to get a breakfast sandwich, this is definitely the slowest Dunkin' I've been to; it wasn't that crowded, just the person doing the sandwiches didn't seem to know what they were doing. When I asked them why I was waiting that long, they did not apologize and tried to put the blame on me. Definitely won't return to this location.

The donuts are always stale, dry, and crusty here, and their coffee tastes so burnt you can barely drink it. There are never enough workers for busy hours (morning rush around 7-9 and lunch rush 12-1), and their food is never fresh, it tastes like old product. The Dunkin inside North Riverside Plaza is much better, their donuts are fresh every day and they are super efficient.

This location has soo much potential to be a solid 5 stars but managements failure to address the main issue is holding them back. This location is in a busy location in the loop and the food prep team continuously drops the ball. There is usually 2 employees who struggle with keeping up with food orders. Just this morning a lady had to walk 5 blocks back from work because she asked for a bagel and instead they gave her a breakfast sandwich. There is an older Indian lady working the food station who completely ignores any attempts to address wrong orders. I even watch her co-worker attempt to guide her and tell her she was making mistakes and she simply ignored him. Either train your staff properly or get this lady off the line.
Every time I go past like 7pm the espresso machine is “down” or they cannot make an iced americano. Its always the same guy that says it too. Very annoying.
